# Public display is non-interactive

TV and wall **display** builds (`apps/display/**`) are **never** operated by someone standing at the screen. Do not add:

- `<button>`, links used as controls, or **`onClick` / `onKeyDown` / `pointer` handlers** that change app state
- Form controls (`input`, `select`, `textarea`) except where the platform forces them and they are hidden/disabled (prefer none)
- **`tabIndex` / `role="button"`** on decorative or informational blocks
- **`history.pushState` / `replaceState` from the display** to drive navigation (URL is chosen when the page is loaded or by external tooling)

## Where control lives

The **host** and **player** apps (or future remote control / CMS) own:

- Choosing layout (venue wall vs single felt, spotlight) via the host app (**`displaySetLayout`** → server **`displayLayout`** to all TVs on the venue code), legacy URL/query for ops setups, or future CMS

## Allowed on display

- Purely **read-only** presentation driven by **socket `state`, `displayLayout`**, props, initial URL/query (ops), set elsewhere — never authored from touches on this screen
- Passive **`useEffect`** timers and animations

## Checklist before merging display changes

- [ ] No interactive elements unless product explicitly exempts a dedicated “operator” build (not default display).
- [ ] Copy does not instruct the audience to “tap” or “click here” on the display.
